# Strategic Strategy: Modularize & Audit (Build 1101E)

This plan shifts our focus to **Modularization (Refactoring)** as the primary priority. By splitting large files into smaller, focused modules, we reduce "Context Noise" and allow AI agents (like Opus 4.6) to perform deeper forensic audits with higher accuracy.

## Proposed Changes

### [Phase 1: UI Modularization] [COMPLETED]
Split [UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.UI.cs](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.UI.cs) (~2246 lines) into:
- [UI.IPC.cs](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.UI.IPC.cs): TCP Server, Client Handlers, and [ProcessIpcCommands](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.UI.IPC.cs#236-993).
- [UI.Compliance.cs](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.UI.Compliance.cs): Compliance Hub, P/L tracking, and Daily Summary logic.
- [UI.Sizing.cs](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.UI.Sizing.cs): ATR Auto-Sizing Engine and Position Sizing math.
- [UI.Callbacks.cs](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.UI.Callbacks.cs): Hotkeys and Chart Click handlers.

### [Phase 2: Order Modularization] [COMPLETED]
Split [UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.cs](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.cs) (~2024 lines) into:
- [Orders.Callbacks.cs](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.Callbacks.cs): [OnOrderUpdate](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.Callbacks.cs#37-530), [OnPositionUpdate](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.Callbacks.cs#636-737), and [OnAccountOrderUpdate](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.Callbacks.cs#531-635).
- [Orders.Management.cs](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.Management.cs): [SubmitBracketOrders](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.Management.cs#37-113), [CleanupPosition](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.Management.cs#677-755), and [ReconcileOrphanedOrders](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.Management.cs#838-969).
- `Orders.Actions.cs`: Hotkey execution logic (ExecuteLong, ExecuteShort, Flatten).
### [Phase 3: Concurrency Hardening]
Implement an event queue or use `TriggerCustomEvent` / `InvokeAsync` to marshal all SIMA callbacks ([OnAccountOrderUpdate](file:///C:/WSGTA/universal-or-strategy/src/UniversalORStrategyV12_002_Dev.Orders.Callbacks.cs#531-635)) to the strategy thread. This prevents "First-Writer-Wins" race conditions between the Master thread and Broker threads.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Verification
- **Compilation Check**: Run `F5` in NinjaTrader after each module split.
- **Thread Audit**: Verify `ManagedThreadId` remains constant during execution updates using debug logs.

### Manual Verification
- **Stress Test**: Slam the IPC with simultaneous `FLATTEN` and `ENTRY` commands during a high-volatility Sim session.
